  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Nav creates a navigation landmark for screen reader navigation</li>
      <li>Use <code>aria-label</code> to distinguish multiple nav elements (e.g., "Main navigation", "Footer navigation")</li>
      <li>Use <code>aria-current="page"</code> on the link to the current page</li>
      <li>Breadcrumbs should use <code>&lt;ol&gt;</code> for ordered sequence semantics</li>
      <li>Ensure sufficient color contrast for link text and focus states</li>
      <li>Links should have visible focus indicators</li>
      <li>Tree navigation uses native <code>&lt;details&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;summary&gt;</code> which are keyboard accessible and announce expand/collapse state</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

